property_description: Experience elevated island living in this stunning penthouse level residence at Ae‘o with extra tall 10 foot ceilings, in one of Honolulu’s most sought-after luxury condominiums in the heart of Ward Village. #PH3907 also comes with storage, making it the perfect home or investment opportunity. As you step inside, you’re greeted by floor-to-ceiling windows that frame sweeping Kaka’ako city, ocean, and mountain views, flooding the space with natural light. The open layout maximizes space & flow, featuring a gourmet kitchen with sleek cabinetry, quartz countertops, and Bosch appliances. The spacious bedroom provides a serene retreat with a walk in closet, while the spa-like bathroom boasts contemporary design. Living at Ae‘o means access to resort-style amenities, including a stunning rooftop terrace, two pools, fitness center, sauna, private movie theater, karaoke room, guest suites, and multiple entertainment areas. Plus, enjoy the convenience of direct access to Whole Foods Market downstairs and being just steps from Ward Village’s premier shopping, dining, and entertainment. Don’t miss your chance to own a luxury home in the heart of Honolulu. Schedule your showing today!

Spacious two-story home set on 2 acres, move-in ready and offering rental income potential and flexible living while you build your dream detached cottage! (Permits approved and ready to go), with CPR potential. In close proximity to Ulumalu Road and Hana Highway, this private property sits at the end of a cul-de-sac and is surrounded by other two-acre parcels. The long, private driveway is lined with majestic old-growth royal palms, an irreplaceable and striking feature that creates a grand sense of arrival. The single-family residence features 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms upstairs, an open floor plan, and seamless indoor-outdoor living and dining spaces. The large kitchen includes bar seating, custom hardwood cabinetry, granite countertops, a gas range, generous storage. Downstairs offers additional living spaces. Recent upgrades include a brand-new roof, stucco exterior, and plaster interior. Enjoy expansive views of the entire property from every window, porch, and lanai. Conveniently located 10 to 15 minutes from Paia Town, Ho‘okipa, and world-class surfing, windsurfing, and kiting beaches, and less than 10 minutes from Haiku Town Center, restaurants, shops, gyms and more. This private paradise is connected to county water and electricity and features mature fruit trees with endless possibilities. No HOA fees. Schedule your private showing today.

265 Uki Uki Loop at Mahana Estates is a premier 0.744-acre parcel that captures the very best of Kapalua’s breathtaking natural beauty and elevated lifestyle. Gently sloping and backing directly onto the 6th hole of the world-famous Plantation Course, this homesite commands unobstructed ocean views across Kapalua Bay to Molokini, while the West Maui Mountains provide a dramatic, verdant backdrop. Experience radiant sunrises over the mountains and unforgettable sunsets over the Pacific. This shovel-ready lot includes completed building plans for a 3,716-square-foot custom estate plus 1,203 square feet of covered lanai space, thoughtfully designed for seamless indoor-outdoor living. The layout features 4 bedrooms, 4.5 bathrooms, a dedicated office, and a separate guest wing with two bedrooms, two bathrooms, and a lock-off option. The outdoor design includes a 27.6' x 18' swimming pool, a separate elevated spa, and a dedicated Baja shelf for sun lounging. A 538-square-foot garage completes the plan. Mahana Estates is a gated, low-density community offering private water, underground utilities, completed infrastructure, and protective height restrictions to preserve view corridors. The lot's gentle topography supports efficient construction and optimal home placement. Just minutes from the world-class amenities of Kapalua Resort, including the Spa Montage, Kapalua Bay and Plantation Golf Courses, scenic hiking trails, and the golden sands of Flemings Beach, Lot 15 offers a rare opportunity to create a legacy estate in one of Maui’s most prestigious resort communities.

Lots of potential with this rare top floor 1 Bedroom/2 Bath "value add" opportunity at Pacific Islander. Property is being rented as two separate studios - each with their own entrance and full bath. Unit 701A has an updated kitchenette but both units have a lot of upside potential - tenants are paying below market rents - $1100/month each. Located in the heart of Waikiki, Pacific Islander is a pet friendly building and is just a short distance from Waikiki Beach as well as numerous shops and tasty restaurants. The building has community laundry and parking stalls are available for rent by waitlist. Bike/Moped/Motorcycle parking is also available. Maintenance Fee includes Electricity, Water/Sewer, Hot Water & Basic Cable and the building also has secured "key fob" entrance. Great opportunity rent out both units or live in one and earn rental income on the other.

property_description: The Hemmeter Estate is a rare, oceanfront estate located at the end of Kaikoo Place on Black Point. Featuring an extraordinary 339.45 linear feet of ocean frontage, this property offers one of the most expansive coastal settings in Hawaii, with exceptional frontage in the heart of Kaikoo. Blending Hawaiian natural elements with European Renaissance–inspired design, the residence showcases exceptional craftsmanship throughout. Set on 35,870 sq ft of land, the estate offers approximately 21,266 sq ft of interior living, complemented by extensive covered and open lanais ideal for entertaining. Highlights include cast-bronze entry doors, coffered Venetian-inspired ceilings, Italian perlato marble staircases and flooring, carved and finished on-site, a two-story oceanfront living room, and refined Art Deco bronze detailing. Amenities include a private theater, library, entertaining lounge, and grotto pool. The expansive primary suite spans nearly 5,000 sq ft and features dual dressing rooms, a fitness area, and sweeping coastline views. The Hemmeter Estate is an irreplaceable oceanfront estate distinguished by scale, privacy, and architectural significance.
